# VoyaVPN line-ending policy.
#
# rustfmt.toml pins `newline_style = "Unix"` (LF), so every Rust source must keep
# LF in the working tree. Without this rule a Windows checkout with
# core.autocrlf=true rewrites LF -> CRLF and `cargo fmt --check` then fails on
# every file ("Incorrect newline style"). Pin Rust sources to LF so the format
# gate stays stable across platforms.
#
# Byte-exact binary fixtures keep their own override in
# tests/fixtures/release/.gitattributes (`* -text`), which wins by path
# specificity.
*.rs text eol=lf

# The IPC bindings are generated by tauri-specta (Typescript export, LF only) and
# `pnpm bindings:check` byte-compares them against a freshly generated copy. Under
# core.autocrlf=true a Windows checkout rewrites LF -> CRLF, which makes that
# byte comparison fail even though the content is identical. Pin the generated
# file to LF so the binding-drift gate stays stable across platforms.
src/ipc/bindings.ts text eol=lf
